.TH "blkdev_issue_write_same" 9 "blkdev_issue_write_same" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blkdev_issue_write_same \- queue a write same operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blkdev_issue_write_same
.BI "(struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "sector_t sector "  ","
.BI "sector_t nr_sects "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ","
.BI "struct page *page "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bdev" 12
target blockdev
.IP "sector" 12
start sector
.IP "nr_sects" 12
number of sectors to write
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
memory allocation flags (for bio_alloc)
.IP "page" 12
page containing data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Issue a write same request for the sectors in question.
